<%- include('partials/head') %> 
<%- include('partials/header') %>

<main>
  <section class="hero-section cultivation-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="hero-title-non-index hero-title-glow">CULTIVATION PROCESS</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">The Science of the Plant</p>
    </div>

    <hr class="neon-divider" />

    <p class="hero-lead">
        We don't just grow cannabis; we engineer an environment where genetic potential is realized. 
        By combining <strong>clinical precision</strong> with <strong>generational wisdom</strong>, 
        we bridge the gap between commercial scale and craft quality.
    </p>
    <hr class="neon-divider" />
  </section>

  <section class="process-section">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">01</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">The Pheno Hunt</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
          <div class="tech-frame">
            <img src="/assets/cultivation/seeds.jpg" alt="Cannabis Seeds" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          <strong>True exotics are hunted, not bought.</strong> While the commercial market relies on generic, tired nursery clones, our cultivation begins at the genetic source: the seed.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          We source exclusive, unreleased seed packs from the world's most respected breeders. It is a rigorous numbers game. Out of hundreds of seeds popped, only a fraction will possess the structure, terpene profile, and raw potency required to earn the Excelsior name.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-vial"></i> Rare Genotype Sourcing</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-microscope"></i> Genetic Expression Tracking</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section alt-bg">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">02</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">Precision Environment</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
           <div class="tech-frame">
             <img src="/assets/cultivation/precision_environment.webp" alt="Atmospheric Control" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          To mimic the plant's natural peak conditions, we exercise <strong>total atmospheric control</strong> across every square foot of our facility.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          By continuously dialing in the Vapor Pressure Deficit (VPD), ambient CO2 levels, and dynamic light spectrums, we remove environmental stress. This allows the plant to focus 100% of its biological energy on producing maximum trichome density and complex terpene profiles.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-temperature-arrow-up"></i> Automated Climate Control</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-cloud"></i> VPD Optimization</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">03</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">Seedling Vigor & Culling</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
          <div class="tech-frame">
             <img src="/assets/cultivation/seed_start.webp" alt="Inspecting Seedlings" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          The nursery phase is strictly survival of the fittest. During the first few weeks of life, seedlings are closely monitored for root development, internodal spacing, and overall vigor.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          We practice a <strong>ruthless culling process</strong>. Any plant exhibiting weak growth, structural flaws, or susceptibility to stress is immediately eliminated from the run. Only the most robust, aggressive growers are allowed to graduate to the vegetative canopy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-seedling"></i> Early Vigor Profiling</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-minus"></i> Strict Culling Protocols</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section alt-bg">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">04</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">Dynamic Nutrient Steering</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
          <div class="tech-frame">
            <img src="/assets/cultivation/nutrient_testing.jpg" alt="Nutrient Mixing" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          Over the multi-month journey through the vegetative and flowering phases, our plants are fed via a customized, highly variable nutrient schedule designed to steer their biological development.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          This is an exact science. We conduct daily testing of the water's pH balance and Parts Per Million (PPM) to track exactly how much nutrient load the roots are absorbing. As the plant transitions into heavy flower, we adjust these microscopic mineral ratios to trigger massive resin production and bud swelling.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-droplet"></i> PPM & pH Daily Testing</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-line"></i> Biological Crop Steering</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">05</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">The Mother Vault</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
           <div class="tech-frame">
             <img src="/assets/cultivation/clone.webp" alt="Lab Technician with Mother Plants" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          When a rare "unicorn" phenotype reveals itself during the flowering phase—displaying flawless structure, heavy yield, and an unforgettable nose—it must be immortalized.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          We take precise cuttings to establish a permanent mother plant in our secure vegetative vault. We maintain a sterile, clinical environment for these elite mothers, ensuring that the specific DNA we hunted is kept vigorous, pathogen-free, and ready for future propagation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-dna"></i> Tissue Culture Prep</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-shield-virus"></i> Pathogen-Free Stock</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section alt-bg">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">06</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">The Harvest Window</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
          <div class="tech-frame">
             <img src="/assets/cultivation/harvesting.jpg" alt="Trichome Inspection" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          Timing is everything. We do not harvest based on a calendar; we harvest based on the biological maturity of the plant's resin glands.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          Using digital microscopy, we inspect the trichome heads daily during late flower. We wait for the precise moment when the trichomes shift from cloudy to amber, indicating peak cannabinoid and terpene development. Once ready, the plants are carefully taken down whole to prevent damaging the delicate volatile oils.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass"></i> Microscopic Trichome Scoping</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-scissors"></i> Whole-Plant Take Down</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">07</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">The Slow Cure</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
          <div class="tech-frame">
            <img src="/assets/cultivation/curing.jpg" alt="Cannabis Drying Room" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          Harvest is not the finish line; it is merely the beginning of the most critical phase: <strong>The Cure</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          While commercial operators rush to market with harsh, heat-dried product, we hang-dry our whole plants in a dark, cool, humidity-controlled vault for weeks. This methodical process allows the chlorophyll to break down naturally, preserving the delicate terpenes and ensuring a remarkably smooth, flavorful smoke.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-snowflake"></i> Cold Cure Environment</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-clock"></i> 30-Day Minimum Processing</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section alt-bg">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">08</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">Precision Hand-Trimming</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
          <div class="tech-frame">
            <img src="/assets/cultivation/trimming.jpeg" alt="Hand Trimming Cannabis" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          Commercial machine trimmers tumble and agitate the flower, knocking off the most potent trichome heads before the product ever reaches the jar. We refuse to compromise our craft for convenience.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          Once the cure is perfected, every single bud is meticulously <strong>hand-trimmed</strong> by our experienced team. This surgical approach preserves the natural, exotic structure of the flower and ensures that the fragile, resin-rich trichomes remain fully intact for the end consumer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-sparkles"></i> 100% Hand-Trimmed</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-gem"></i> Trichome Preservation</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="process-section">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      
      <div class="step-badge">09</div>
      <h3 class="process-title">Preservation & Packaging</h3>
      
      <div class="process-content clearfix">
        <div class="process-image-wrapper">
          <div class="tech-frame">
            <img src="/assets/cultivation/vacuum_sealed.jpg" alt="Premium Packaging" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="copy-text">
          The final step is protecting the genetics we spent months perfecting. We view our packaging as a biological vault, designed to halt degradation and freeze the flower at its absolute peak.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          To ensure the product reaches our customers in pristine condition, it is immediately sealed in premium, airtight glass with strict micro-climate humidity control. This locks in the moisture and volatile terpenes, guaranteeing that when you open a jar of Northern Legacy flower, it is as fresh as the day it left the curing room.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="tech-list">
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-jar"></i> Micro-Climate Sealing</li>
         <li><i class="fa-solid fa-lock"></i> Terpene Lock Tech</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="petition" class="petition-wrapper">
    <div class="narrow-container">
      <div class="petition-intro">
        <h2 class="petition-header header-glow">We Need Your Help</h2>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          Our plants are thriving. The science is ready. 
          <strong>Help us open the 1000 Islands' first cannabis dispensary.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="petition-card-monolith">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3>Community Action Gauge</h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="stats-row">
            <p class="target-text">Goal: <strong>500 Signatures</strong></p>
            
            <% if (typeof sigCount !== 'undefined' && sigCount >= 20) { %>
              <p class="current-count" id="signature-text">Current: <strong><%= sigCount %></strong></p>
            <% } else { %>
              <p class="current-count" id="signature-text" style="display: none;">Current: <strong><%= typeof sigCount !== 'undefined' ? sigCount : 0 %></strong></p>
            <% } %>
          </div>

          <div class="progress-bar">
            <div class="progress-fill" id="signature-progress" 
                 style="width: <%= typeof sigCount !== 'undefined' ? Math.min((sigCount / 500) * 100, 100) + '%' : '0%' %>">
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <p class="sub-text">We are ready to serve. Tell the State to let us open.</p>
          
          <a href="https://c.org/HrGp2jzv8B" target="_blank" class="btn-petition btn-large">
            Sign The Petition <i class="fa-solid fa-pen-nib"></i>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>